de.esoco.gwt.shared

Class Command<T extends de.esoco.data.element.DataElement<?>,R extends de.esoco.data.element.DataElement<?>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.esoco.gwt.shared.Command<T,R>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Command<T extends de.esoco.data.element.DataElement<?>,R extends de.esoco.data.element.DataElement<?>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class defines a command for a CommandService. The type parameter T defines the type of the input value for the command and the parameter R stands for the datatype of the command result. New instances are created with the factory method newInstance(String) and are must to be defined as static singleton constants which should have the same name as the instance. The factory method enforces this by checking that not two commands have the same name.
